{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The embedding vector produced for a given query string has the correct dimensionality for the vector database index.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The failure boundary is between the live embedding provider output and the live index schema contract. A mock embedding client can hide real model-dimension mismatches (e.g., model/version/config drift), so a real API call is needed.","test_description":"Run an API-level test that sends a real query through the production embedding client against a real/staging embedding endpoint, fetches index dimension from the actual vector DB metadata endpoint, and asserts returned embedding length equals index dimension.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.35,"System":0.45,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The similarity search returns results ordered by descending cosine similarity score.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This behavior is primarily about wiring between query embedding, vector-search adapter, and ranking/serialization logic. It is a module-boundary failure, but does not require real external APIs if a local vector index fixture is used.","test_description":"Set up a local test vector index with known vectors and deterministic expected cosine scores, execute the search module end-to-end (embedding stub allowed), and assert scores are monotonically non-increasing and item order matches descending cosine similarity.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The LLM re-ranking step changes the order of at least some results compared to the raw similarity ranking when the query has nuanced intent.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real LLM judgment for nuanced intent. Mocked rerankers can trivially force reorder and hide genuine model behavior; outcomes can vary across runs/prompts/model versions.","test_description":"Use a fixed nuanced-query benchmark set and real reranking LLM calls; for each case compare raw similarity order vs reranked order and assert at least one pairwise order inversion occurs in a minimum percentage of cases over repeated runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A query with no close matches in the database returns an empty result set rather than low-relevance noise.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The key failure is thresholding and result-filter behavior across search output and API response assembly. This is best caught where modules interact; pure unit tests can miss threshold wiring/config errors.","test_description":"Seed a local vector DB fixture where all candidate similarities for a test query are below the relevance cutoff, run the search API handler through similarity stage (rerank disabled/bypassed for empty candidates), and assert response contains zero results.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The end-to-end latency from receiving the query to returning re-ranked results stays below 2 seconds for the median case.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This is an end-to-end performance SLO dependent on real HTTP calls, network, serialization, and service orchestration. Mocking dependencies will systematically understate latency and hide real regressions.","test_description":"Run a system performance test against a deployed environment with real embedding and reranking providers, execute a representative query mix (sufficient sample size), measure full request latency at API boundary, and assert p50 < 2000 ms.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.82,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
